HEADWORD: Oxhide
<hw>Ox"hide`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The skin
of an ox, or leather made from it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(O. Eng. Law)</fld> <def>A measure of land. See 3d
<er>Hide</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oxid</ent>⟦br⟧
